## 6. Summary of Key Factors Driving Oil Price Increases

| Factor                         | Description                                                   | Impact on Price                   |
|--------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Demand Recovery                | Post-pandemic economic rebound increasing oil consumption     | Upward pressure                  |
| OPEC+ Production Management    | Coordinated supply cuts and cautious output increases         | Supports higher prices           |
| U.S. Shale Production          | Limited growth due to capital discipline and infrastructure   | Supply constraint                |
| Geopolitical Risks             | Sanctions, conflicts, and political instability               | Price volatility and spikes      |
| Energy Transition              | Reduced investment in new oil capacity                         | Long-term supply concerns        |
| Alternative Energy Prices      | High natural gas and coal prices leading to oil substitution  | Increased oil demand             |
| Supply Chain Bottlenecks       | Logistics and storage issues                                   | Supply-demand imbalance          |
| Market Sentiment and Speculation | Traders' expectations and futures market dynamics             | Price volatility                 |

